stylometry: The best way to think about safety stock in my mind is like an insurance policy.  Safety stock comes into play when we are trying to figure out how much inventory we need to order of a certain product.  This term will often come up in the restaurant business all the time.  For example at Rubys when we do inventory we have to think about how many burgers we need to order to cover ourselves throughout the week and most importantly on the weekends during the big dinner rushes.  We want to make sure that we have enough on site so that we do not run out.  Therefore, when we order them we order just a little bit extra to cover ourselves. SS = z*standard deviation.
